#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:11
msgid "IntelOneapi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:15
msgid "Contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:18
msgid "oneAPI packages in Spack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:20
msgid ""
"Spack can install and use the Intel oneAPI products. You may either use "
"spack to install the oneAPI tools or use the `Intel installers`_. After "
"installation, you may use the tools directly, or use Spack to build packages "
"with the tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:25
msgid ""
"The Spack Python class ``IntelOneapiPackage`` is a base class that is used "
"by ``IntelOneapiCompilers``, ``IntelOneapiMkl``, ``IntelOneapiTbb`` and "
"other classes to implement the oneAPI packages. Search for ``oneAPI`` at "
"`packages.spack.io <https://packages.spack.io>`_ for the full list of "
"available oneAPI packages, or use::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:31
msgid "spack list -d oneAPI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:33
msgid "For more information on a specific package, do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:35
msgid "spack info --all <package-name>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:37
msgid ""
"Intel no longer releases new versions of Parallel Studio, which can be used "
"in Spack via the :ref:`intelpackage`. All of its components can now be found "
"in oneAPI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:42
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:45
msgid "Building a Package With icx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:47
msgid ""
"In this example, we build patchelf with ``icc`` and ``icx``. The compilers "
"are installed with spack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:50
#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:92
msgid "Install the oneAPI compilers::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:52
#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:94
msgid "spack install intel-oneapi-compilers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:54
msgid "Add the compilers to your ``compilers.yaml`` so spack can use them::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:56
msgid ""
"spack compiler add `spack location -i intel-oneapi-compilers`/compiler/"
"latest/bin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:58
#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:101
msgid "Verify that the compilers are available::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:60
#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:103
msgid "spack compiler list"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:62
msgid ""
"Note that 2024 and later releases do not include ``icc``. Before 2024, the "
"package layout was different::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:65
msgid ""
"spack compiler add `spack location -i intel-oneapi-compilers`/compiler/"
"latest/linux/bin/intel64\n"
"spack compiler add `spack location -i intel-oneapi-compilers`/compiler/"
"latest/linux/bin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:68
msgid ""
"The ``intel-oneapi-compilers`` package includes 2 families of compilers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:71
msgid ""
"``intel``: ``icc``, ``icpc``, ``ifort``. Intel's *classic* compilers. 2024 "
"and later releases contain ``ifort``, but not ``icc`` and ``icpc``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:74
msgid ""
"``oneapi``: ``icx``, ``icpx``, ``ifx``. Intel's new generation of compilers "
"based on LLVM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:77
msgid "To build the ``patchelf`` Spack package with ``icc``, do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:79
msgid "spack install patchelf%intel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:81
msgid "To build with with ``icx``, do ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:83
msgid "spack install patchelf%oneapi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:87
msgid "Using oneAPI Spack environment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:89
msgid ""
"In this example, we build lammps with ``icx`` using Spack environment for "
"oneAPI packages created by Intel. The compilers are installed with Spack "
"like in example above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:96
msgid "Add the compilers to your ``compilers.yaml`` so Spack can use them::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:98
msgid ""
"spack compiler add `spack location -i intel-oneapi-compilers`/compiler/"
"latest/bin\n"
"spack compiler add `spack location -i intel-oneapi-compilers`/compiler/"
"latest/bin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:105
msgid ""
"Clone `spack-configs <https://github.com/spack/spack-configs>`_ repo and "
"activate Intel oneAPI CPU environment::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:107
msgid ""
"git clone https://github.com/spack/spack-configs\n"
"spack env activate spack-configs/INTEL/CPU\n"
"spack concretize -f"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:111
msgid ""
"`Intel oneAPI CPU environment <https://github.com/spack/spack-configs/blob/"
"main/INTEL/CPU/spack.yaml>`_  contains applications tested and validated by "
"Intel, this list is constantly extended. And currently it supports:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:113
msgid "`Devito <https://www.devitoproject.org/>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:114
msgid "`GROMACS <https://www.gromacs.org/>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:115
msgid "`HPCG <https://www.hpcg-benchmark.org/>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:116
msgid "`HPL <https://netlib.org/benchmark/hpl/>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:117
msgid "`LAMMPS <https://www.lammps.org/#gsc.tab=0>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:118
msgid "`OpenFOAM <https://www.openfoam.com/>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:119
msgid "`Quantum Espresso <https://www.quantum-espresso.org/>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:120
msgid "`STREAM <https://www.cs.virginia.edu/stream/>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:121
msgid "`WRF <https://github.com/wrf-model/WRF>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:123
msgid "To build lammps with oneAPI compiler from this environment just run::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:125
msgid "spack install lammps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:127
msgid "Compiled binaries can be find using::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:129
msgid "spack cd -i lammps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:131
msgid "You can do the same for all other applications from this environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:135
msgid "Using oneAPI MPI to Satisfy a Virtual Dependence"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:137
msgid ""
"The ``hdf5`` package works with any compatible MPI implementation. To build "
"``hdf5`` with Intel oneAPI MPI do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:140
msgid "spack install hdf5 +mpi ^intel-oneapi-mpi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:143
msgid "Using Externally Installed oneAPI Tools"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:145
msgid ""
"Spack can also use oneAPI tools that are manually installed with `Intel "
"Installers`_.  The procedures for configuring Spack to use external "
"compilers and libraries are different."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:150
msgid "Compilers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:152
msgid ""
"To use the compilers, add some information about the installation to "
"``compilers.yaml``. For most users, it is sufficient to do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:155
msgid "spack compiler add /opt/intel/oneapi/compiler/latest/bin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:157
msgid ""
"Adapt the paths above if you did not install the tools in the default "
"location. After adding the compilers, using them is the same as if you had "
"installed the ``intel-oneapi-compilers`` package. Another option is to "
"manually add the configuration to ``compilers.yaml`` as described in :ref:"
"`Compiler configuration <compiler-config>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:164
msgid "Before 2024, the directory structure was different::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:166
msgid ""
"spack compiler add /opt/intel/oneapi/compiler/latest/linux/bin/intel64\n"
"spack compiler add /opt/intel/oneapi/compiler/latest/linux/bin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:171
msgid "Libraries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:173
msgid ""
"If you want Spack to use oneMKL that you have installed without Spack in the "
"default location, then add the following to ``~/.spack/packages.yaml``, "
"adjusting the version as appropriate::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:177
msgid ""
"intel-oneapi-mkl:\n"
"  externals:\n"
"  - spec: intel-oneapi-mkl@2021.1.1\n"
"    prefix: /opt/intel/oneapi/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:184
msgid "Using oneAPI Tools Installed by Spack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:186
msgid ""
"Spack can be a convenient way to install and configure compilers and "
"libraries, even if you do not intend to build a Spack package. If you want "
"to build a Makefile project using Spack-installed oneAPI compilers, then use "
"spack to configure your environment::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:191
msgid "spack load intel-oneapi-compilers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:193
msgid "And then you can build with::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:195
msgid "CXX=icpx make"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:197
msgid "You can also use Spack-installed libraries. For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:199
msgid "spack load intel-oneapi-mkl"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:201
msgid ""
"Will update your environment CPATH, LIBRARY_PATH, and other environment "
"variables for building an application with oneMKL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:205
msgid "More information"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/inteloneapipackage.rst:207
msgid ""
"This section describes basic use of oneAPI, especially if it has changed "
"compared to Parallel Studio. See :ref:`intelpackage` for more information "
"on :ref:`intel-virtual-packages`, :ref:`intel-unrelated-packages`, :ref:"
"`intel-integrating-external-libraries`, and :ref:`using-mkl-tips`."
msgstr ""
